# Phase 3: SSE Broadcast Integration – Tasks & Alignment Brief

**Spec**: [../../better-agents-spec.md](../../better-agents-spec.md)
**Plan**: [../../better-agents-plan.md](../../better-agents-plan.md)
**Date**: 2026-01-27
**Phase Slug**: `phase-3-sse-broadcast-integration`

---

## Executive Briefing

### Purpose
This phase wires up the complete event flow from adapters through storage, API routes, SSE broadcast, and frontend hooks. It's the critical integration layer that connects Phase 2's adapter event parsing with Phase 4's UI components—without this, the newly emitted tool_call, tool_result, and thinking events would never reach the browser.

### What We're Building
End-to-end event pipeline integration:

**API Route (`/api/agents/run`):**
- Extend `broadcastAgentEvent()` to handle `tool_call`, `tool_result`, `thinking` events
- Integrate `EventStorageService` to persist events before broadcast (per Critical Discovery 01)
- Ensure all events include `sessionId` for client-side routing (per ADR-0007)

**useAgentSSE Hook:**
- Add new callbacks: `onToolCall`, `onToolResult`, `onThinking`
- Implement event fetching on connect to handle race conditions (per Critical Discovery 08)
- Refactor listener management to AbortController pattern (per Medium Discovery 09)

**Session State:**
- Extend message schema with `contentType` discrimination
- Update session state reducer for new message types

### User Value
When an agent runs a tool, users immediately see "Running Bash: ls -la" appear in the UI. When reasoning happens, users see the thinking process unfold. Events persist through page refresh—no more lost context.

### Example
**Before**: Claude runs `npm test` → User sees only "All tests passed" text response
**After**:
```
[SSE: agent_tool_call]    → UI shows "Running npm test..."
[SSE: agent_tool_result]  → UI shows "✓ 2055 tests passed" with output
[SSE: agent_text_delta]   → UI shows "All tests passed" text
[Storage: persisted]      → Refresh page → All events restored
```

---

## Objectives & Scope

### Objective
Wire up the three-layer event pipeline as specified in the plan, satisfying:
- **AC8**: Tool execution status updates in real-time via SSE (user sees "Running..." then "Complete")
- **AC9**: Long tool outputs stream progressively, not all-at-once after completion
- **AC10**: Text responses continue to stream normally alongside tool activity
- **AC17**: Events are persisted to `.chainglass/workspaces/<slug>/data/` as NDJSON files
- **AC18**: Page refresh reloads session events from server (no data loss)
- **AC19**: `GET /events?since=<id>` returns only events after the specified ID

### Goals

- ✅ Extend `broadcastAgentEvent()` with `tool_call`, `tool_result`, `thinking` cases
- ✅ Integrate `EventStorageService` into run route (persist before broadcast)
- ✅ Add `onToolCall`, `onToolResult`, `onThinking` callbacks to `useAgentSSE`
- ✅ Implement event fetching on SSE connect (race condition mitigation)
- ✅ Refactor listener cleanup to AbortController pattern
- ✅ Extend session message schema with `contentType` field
- ✅ Update session state reducer for new event types
- ✅ Deduplicate events by ID (fetch + SSE overlap)
- ✅ Existing text streaming continues to work (regression tests pass)

### Non-Goals (Scope Boundaries)

- ❌ UI components (Phase 4) — no React components in this phase
- ❌ Adapter modifications (Phase 2 complete) — adapters already emit events
- ❌ Performance optimization — focus on correctness first
- ❌ Virtualization for large event logs — defer to future if needed
- ❌ Event compression or batching — simplicity over optimization
- ❌ WebSocket alternative (per ADR-0007: SSE is the chosen pattern)
- ❌ Multi-workspace support — hardcoded "default" workspace for now

